column5: I put a request up on Facebook to see if anyone was interested joining me for a muskie fish today and Patrick answered with a heck ya! It was cold and windy when we launched and it didn't get any better from that. Casting was pretty dead with no follows and boat control tough with the wind so we switched back and forth from casting to trolling. Water temp was 52.9 and it was full of floating crap. Right at the 10:15 am moon rise while trolling a 12' to 15' break line this gorgeous lady payed us a visit. Not much of a fight but just stayed deep and head shakes.  Tried to follow it up with a second fish but no takers.  49" and no girth!
sweet. when the ice arrives ya got a great memory
What a beauty, too bad there was no fight.
Nothing wrong with that fish!  Beauty!
Nice fish Matt worth the trip
pig.  so you believe in the moon stuff........
pig.  so you believe in the moon stuff........ Absolutely yes I do. Have many catches on the moon cycles.  I always and I mean always leave my best spots for peak moon times
Girth or not, a 49"er ain't nothing to sneeze at.   Congrats on weathering the conditions.
Very nice fish Matt, and I agree with you 100% about the moon phases.

Girth or not, a 49"er ain't nothing to sneeze at.   Congrats on weathering the conditions.  Sorry, actually what I meant was that we did not measure the girth, but she was a nice fat fish for sure! Very healthy and looked like it was starting to fatten up for the winter.
